
This program requires either giflib or pnglib to do anything useful.

Giflib can be obtained at http://www.ccil.org/~esr/giflib/.  Be certain 
that you do not install a broken version of the library that has all of 
the encode functions disabled, such as ungiflib.  No one uses GIF anymore
so just use PNG and be happy.

  To build the main library, do:

     $ ./configure
     $ make 
     $ sudo make install

  This will install libansiconv into $prefix/lib (often /usr/local/lib), and 
a program called ansiconv to $prefix/bin.  For PHP support, after installing
the library do:

    $ cd php
    $ ./configure
    $ make && sudo make install

  Using the php module is as easy as:
  <?php 
    if(!extension_loaded('ansiconv')) {
	    dl('ansiconv.' . PHP_SHLIB_SUFFIX);
    }
    header('Content-type: image/png');
    $fp=fopen($sanitized_path, 'rb'); 

    // arguments are: 
    //   resource (file pointer)
    //   input type (0=ansi, 1=bin, 2=idf)
    //   output type (0=png, 1=gif)
    //   use thumbnail mode (optional)
    ansiconv_convert($fp, 0, 0, false);  
  ?>
